    <stitle>CE 200, CE 300 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE - Valance Panels</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Valance Panels</title>
        <para>The valance panels are separate bolt-on panels that complete the wheel well opening and surround the
            headlight assemblies. The panels are fiberglass-composite, removable parts that are bolted to the underside
            of the fender assembly flange and headlight housing lower flange.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the two lower mounting bolts under the headlight housing flange (
                <hotlnk document="s09009_31.xml" xrefid="f0900939">Figure 41, Item 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the bolts securing the valance panel to the headlight housing flange.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the two mounting bolts on the underside of the fender panel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900938">Figure 40, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the mounting screws and remove the valance panel.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure for the opposite side valance panel.</para>
        </step1>
